- var pagetype = "styleguide"
- var page = "Grid"

doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    include ./layout/_head.jade
  body(class='#{pagetype}')
    header.styleguide-header
      include ./layout/_navbar.jade
      
    main.styleguide-container(role='main')

      .container
        .row 
          .col.s12
            .section
              h2.header Container
              p The container class is important in laying out content. It allows you to center your page content. The container class is set to a maximum of 960px. It helps you center and contain your page content. We use the container to contain our body content.
              
              p 
                :markdown
                  To add a container just put your content inside a `<div>` tag with a `container` class. Here's an example of how your page might be set up.
              
              pre      
                code.language-markup.
                  <main class="main-container">
                    <div class="container">
                      <!-- Page Content goes here --> 
                    </div>
                  </main>
        
            .section
              h2.header Grid
              p Our standard grid has 12 columns. No matter the size of the browser, each of these columns will always have an equal width.
              
              p Columns are applied with the `.col` class. A column always resides in a `.row` to clearfix the float. On all devices you can use the class `.s1` to `.s12`, where the number stands for the amount of colums to span. This is always based on the 12 column grid.
              
              p The letter `s` here stands for small screens. Since we use a mobile-first approach, we define the mobile layout as default.
              
              h4 Screen sizes
              p For the breakpoints $small and $medium, which are defined in the sass file we have individual grid override options. You can use `.m` for the `$small` breakpoint and `.l` for the `$medium breakpoint`. This give you the flexibility to have different layouts on mobile, tablet and desktop screen sizes.
              
              .row
                .col.s12.m8.l6.grid-example
                  span.flow-text I am full-width on mobile, 75% on tablet and 50% on desktop (col s12 m8 l6)
                .col.s12.m4.l6.grid-example
                  span.flow-text I am full-width on mobile, 25% on tablet and 50% on desktop (col s12 m4 l6)
                
            .section
              h2.header Base layout
              p Our base layout consist of the following regions. Below you can see the layout.
              
              ul.list 
                li Header: primary navigation, user menu, site search
                li Breadcrumbs 
                li Hero: displays an overview of the page
                li Secondary navigation: section specific navigation
                li Main content: holds the content of the page
                li Complementary: sidebar with block such as filters or other actions
                li Footer: closing block of the page
            
              .browser-window
                .top-bar
                  .circles
                   #close-circle.circle
                   #minimize-circle.circle
                   #maximize-circle.circle
                .content
                  .row
                    #site-layout-example-header.col.s12
                      p Header
                  .row.only-desktop
                    #site-layout-example-breadcrumb.col.l12
                      p Breadcrumbs
                  .row
                    #site-layout-example-hero.col.s12
                      p Hero
                      p.flat-text.inline25
                      p.flat-text.inline25
                      p.flat-text.inline25
                  .row
                    #site-layout-example-secondary.col.s12
                      p Secondary navigation
                      p.flat-text.inline25 
                      p.flat-text.inline25
                      p.flat-text.inline25
                  .row
                    #site-layout-example-main.col.s12.m9
                      p main content 
                      p.flat-text-header 
                      p.flat-text
                      p.flat-text
                      p.flat-text
                    #site-layout-example-aside.col.s12.m3
                      p Complementary
                      p.flat-text.small
                      p.flat-text
                      p.flat-text
                  .row
                    #site-layout-example-footer.col.s12
                      p Footer

    include ./layout/_scripts.jade
